public abstract class Naturalist

Constructor Detail

Naturalist

public Naturalist()
Default constructor for the naturalist. Warning: When the constructor is called, the world map has not yet been initialized, so calls to getLocation() will return null.

moveTo

public void moveTo(Node dest)
            throws IllegalMoveException
Move the naturalist to destination dest. If dest is the current location, do nothing. Throw an IllegalMoveException if current location is not adjacent to dest or it is blocked by water or trees.

Throws:
IllegalMoveException

listAnimalsPresent

public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> listAnimalsPresent()
= a list of the names of the animals present at the current location.

A good way to use this method is as follows:
Collection animals= listAnimalsPresent();
for (String s : animals) {
collect(s);
}

But be sure you don't collect an animal if the navigator already holds the maximum number of animals that can be held at one time.

collect

public void collect(java.lang.String n)
             throws CapacityExceededException,
                    SpecimenNotFoundException
Collect an animal named n from the current location. Throw a CapacityExceededException if the naturalist is already carrying the maximum number of animals, as given by MAX_ANIMAL_CAPACITY. Throw a SpecimenNotFoundException if animal n is not present.

Throws:
CapacityExceededException
SpecimenNotFoundException

dropAll

public void dropAll()
Drop all animals currently being carried. If the current location is the ship, animals will disappear and score will be increased.
